  "prompt": "Which is the best recommended book for CA-CPT?",
  "response": "For the CA-CPT (Chartered Accountancy - Common Proficiency Test), one of the highly recommended books is \"CPT - General Economics\" by Dr. S.K. Aggarwal and \"CPT - Quantitative Aptitude\" by Dr. T.P. Padmanabhan. These books are known for their comprehensive coverage of the syllabus, clear explanations, and numerous practice problems. Additionally, study materials provided by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) are essential and should be used alongside other resources. It's also beneficial to solve previous years' question papers and take mock tests to better prepare for the exam.",
